news.title: Blackstone buys office building in Paris for $819 million
news.para: Blackstone has confirmed its acquisition of the Centre d'Affaires, a prestigious office building in Paris, for approximately 700 million euros. This purchase from Union Investments signals a renewed investor interest in prime office properties following a pandemic-induced slump.

news.title: Kartik Aaryan makes debut land investment with 2,000 sq ft plot in Alibaug
news.para: Alibaug has seen increased real estate and tourism activity in recent years, supported by infrastructure upgrades such as the Mumbai Trans Harbour Link (MTHL), the Navi Mumbai International Airport, and improved road and jetty connectivity. These infrastructure related developments have driven demand for premium plotted projects and second homes, positioning Alibaug as a preferred residential location near Mumbai.

news.title: Arkade Developers acquires Woollen & Textile Industries
news.para: Arkade Developers has acquired 100% shareholding in Woollen and Textile Industries which includes 14,363.60 sq meters land parcel for a total consideration for the deal is ₹148 crore.

news.title: MUFG to launch $680 million Japan real estate fund
news.para: Mitsubishi UFJ Financial Group is set to launch a 100 billion yen fund to invest in Japanese real estate, capitalizing on rising property prices and anticipated interest rate hikes. The fund will target underperforming assets, focusing on mid-sized offices, residential properties, and hotels in major cities like Tokyo and Osaka.

news.title: Final land plan schedule for Coimbatore metro to be completed within two months
news.para: Coimbatore Metro Rail project is progressing swiftly, with CMRL expected to finalize land plans, including asset valuation, for its two corridors within two months. An urgent plan for a congested 1.4km stretch has been submitted for validation. Surveys and mapping are complete, and a double-decker construction on Avinashi Road is under consideration, pending further studies and approvals.

news.title: Received consent for 50% land of new Purandar airport: District collector
news.para: Nearly half the farmers in seven affected villages have consented to land acquisition for the proposed Purandar airport, according to District Collector Jitendra Dudi. Around 1,450 acres out of the revised 3,000 acres have been approved for acquisition.

news.title: Jawaharlal Nehru's first official residence sold for ₹1,100 crore
news.para: Jawaharlal Nehru's former residence on Motilal Nehru Marg is poised for a record-breaking sale. A businessman prominent in the beverage industry is reportedly acquiring the 14,973 square-meter property for approximately ₹1,100 crore. The property, owned by Raj Kumari Kackar and Bina Rani of a Rajasthani royal family, is undergoing due diligence, signaling the deal's final stages.

news.title: Karnataka housing board plans 772-acre housing project in Devanahalli
news.para: Karnataka Housing Board plans a 772-acre housing project near Devanahalli's ITIR to meet rising residential demand, focusing on affordable homes for economically weaker sections. The project, spanning five villages, faces potential land acquisition challenges, reminiscent of past farmer protests that led to the scrapping of a larger acquisition.

news.title: Lucknow development body lodges FIR after 18 get fake letter for PMAY homes
news.para: The Lucknow Development Authority (LDA) filed a police complaint after discovering that 18 individuals were defrauded of a significant amount of money under the guise of the Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana in Basant Kunj Yojana. Victims were deceived with forged allotment letters and registration certificates.

news.title: Bengaluru development body says RERA order doesn't apply to us, cites statutory status
news.para: The Bangalore Development Authority (BDA) claims it's not under Rera's jurisdiction, arguing its site allotments are contractual and governed by its own 1984 rules. This comes after Rera labeled the Nadaprabhu Kempegowda Layout (NKPL) project as "lapsed" due to delays, leaving over 10,000 families in limbo.

news.title: China Evergrande liquidators apply for receivers to identify founder's assets
news.para: China Evergrande's liquidators are pursuing founder Hui Ka Yan, seeking court-appointed receivers to locate his undisclosed assets. This action aims to recover $6 billion in dividends and remuneration paid to Hui and other executives before the company's collapse. Hui, currently detained, faces accusations of non-disclosure, while liquidators have recovered only a fraction of the $45 billion owed to creditors.

news.title: JSW Cement's profit before exceptional item & tax at ₹164.74 crore in Q1 FY26
news.para: JSW Cement Ltd witnessed a significant surge in profit before exceptional items and tax, reaching Rs 164.74 crore in the June 2025 quarter. This marks a substantial increase from Rs 8.14 crore in the corresponding period last year. Revenue from operations also climbed by 7.77% to Rs 1,559.82 crore.

news.title: Delhi civic body's Suniyo property tax scheme nets ₹304 crore in three months
news.para: The Municipal Corporation of Delhi's (MCD) Suniyo property tax amnesty scheme has yielded impressive results, collecting Rs 304 crore in just three months. This figure surpasses the previous Samriddhi scheme's collection by over three-and-a-half times. The Suniyo scheme attracted a significantly larger number of taxpayers, with 1,02,142 people participating compared to the Samriddhi scheme's 38,805.

news.title: New Zealand to ease restrictions on foreign home buyers
news.para: New Zealand is set to partially lift its ban on foreign home buyers, allowing wealthy investors with 'golden visas' to purchase properties worth at least $3 million. Prime Minister Christopher Luxon says this move aims to attract overseas investment and stimulate economic growth during a recession.

news.title: Report says M-sand causing indoor temperatures to rise
news.para: A state legislature committee report linking M-sand to rising indoor temperatures has sparked controversy in Bengaluru's construction sector. Experts refute the claim, citing a lack of scientific evidence and emphasizing the importance of design, ventilation, and quality control. They warn against reverting to river sand due to environmental concerns.

news.title: Maharashtra promises favourable policies for real estate
news.para: Maharashtra government will focus on infrastructure and housing policies. Meghana Sakore Bordikar spoke at the Naredco National Convention in Delhi. Niranjan Hiranandani wants the real estate sector to grow by 15% annually. The government is prioritizing sustainable development and water resource management. Smita Patil requested policy support for the real estate industry.

news.title: WeWork India lease out 22,700 sq ft to Chargebee in Chennai
news.para: WeWork India has leased 22,000 sq ft of space to Chargebee at WeWork Ramanujan Intellion Park in Chennai, following Chargebee's move of its Ireland office to WeWork in Dublin earlier in 2025. WeWork India had leased two centers in July 2025, one in Pune and the other in Chennai, expanding its presence across eight cities with over one lakh desks.

news.title: UrbanVault leases 80,000 sq ft space at Manyata Tech Park, Bengaluru
news.para: UrbanVault has expanded its presence by leasing 80,000 sq ft at Manyata Tech Park in Bengaluru, offering over 2,000 seats with prices starting at Rs 10,000 per month. The workspace provider, which reported a ₹120 crore turnover in FY25, has secured clients like Cloud Odyssey and SRM Tech. This move increases UrbanVault's portfolio to over 2.

news.title: Hema Malini sells two apartments for ₹12.50 crore in Mumbai
news.para: Veteran actress Hema Malini has recently sold two apartments in Mumbai's Oberoi Springs for a combined ₹12.50 crore. Each apartment, boasting a carpet area of 847 sq ft, was sold for ₹6.25 crore, inclusive of one car parking space.

news.title: Nuvoco Vistas to invest ₹200 crore to add four MMTPA capacity
news.para: Nuvoco Vistas Corp plans a ₹200 crore investment to expand cement grinding capacity by four MMTPA at the Arasmeta plant, alongside upgrades at other facilities. These strategic moves, including the Vadraj Cement acquisition, aim to solidify their leadership in the East and increase market share in the West and North.
